      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       Implements a motor pilot based on API221 and an externally controlled motor.
      4           *
      5           * @details     This module uses API221MotionCtrl to control an external motor controller. It
      6           *              accepts two types of commands: simple and normal commands. They are identified
      7           *              using bit 7 of the first byte of the command. 0 = Simple command. 1 = Custom
      8           *              command.
      9           *
     10           *              Simple Commands:
     11           *                  EXTERNAL_MOTOR_NO_COMMAND: 0x00
     12           *                  This command indicates that no module requested anything for the external
     13           *                  motor. In this case, the pilot will turn off the motor.
     14           *
     15           *                  EXTERNAL_MOTOR_NO_CHANGE: 0x01
     16           *                  This command indicates that the application requested that the pilot maintain
     17           *                  the most recent command. In this case, the pilot will not do anything.
     18           *
     19           *                  EXTERNAL_MOTOR_STOP: 0x02, deceleration (lo,hi)
     20           *                  The pilot will send the Stop command with the specified deceleration. However,
     21           *                  if this command is a copy of the previously sent command, then this command
     22           *                  will do nothing.
     23           *
     24           *                  EXTERNAL_MOTOR_RUN: 0x03, velocity (lo,hi), acceleration (lo,hi)
     25           *                  The pilot will send the Run command with the specified velocity and
     26           *                  acceleration. However, if this command is a copy of the previously sent
     27           *                  command, then this command will do nothing.
     28           *
     29           *              Custom commands:
     30           *                  Always the same format: 0x80 + size, buffer
     31           *              These commands are used to perform custom platform-specific behaviors. Neither
     32           *              this module, nor the API221 module have any code to implement these custom
     33           *              behaviors. The platform-specific code on the API221 server will parse the buffer.
     34           *
     35           *              Custom commands are only expected to be set on change. In between changes, the
     36           *              EXTERNAL_MOTOR_NO_CHANGE simple command should be sent.
     37           *
     38           *              If the external motor control node is not connected on the Reveal communications
     39           *              bus, then the ExternalMotorPilot will save the command until the node connects. It will
     40           *              then send the most recent command.
     41           *
     42           * Setting file data structures for ExternalMotorPilot
     43           *      ExternalMotorPilot Configuration
     44           *              | 7 | 6 | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 | 7 | 6 | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 |
     45           *      +0000h  |        Refresh_Seconds        |          Motor_Index          |
     46           *      +0001h  |         Deceleration          | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 |
     47           *
     48           *          Refer to the #EXTERNAL_MOTOR_PILOT_SF_CONFIG_TYPE for descriptions of the fields.
     49           *
     50              @startuml{ExternalMotorPilot_sm.png}
     51                  title External Motor Pilot State Machine
     52                  ' Use state = Emp_This->State
     53          
     54                  [*] --> Disconnected
     55          
     56                  Disconnected : do / CheckForMcuConnect()
     57                  Disconnected --> Connected : evMcuConnected\n/ SendProcessed()
     58          
     59                  Connected : do / CheckForMcuDisconnect()
     60                  Connected --> Disconnected : evMcuDisconnected
     61              @enduml
     62           *
     63           * @copyright   Copyright 2016 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     64           */
     65          
